# Feature: Login & Authentication

## Feature Description
This feature enables users to securely log into their SwiftPay accounts using their credentials. It supports authentication mechanisms such as password verification and two-factor authentication (2FA).

## Functional Goals
- Secure login using email/phone + password
- Support biometric login (optional, future update)
- Integrate optional two-factor authentication
- Prevent brute-force login attempts
- Logout functionality

## Business Value
Security is essential in financial applications. A reliable login system protects user accounts, builds trust, and ensures compliance with financial regulations.

## User Story
As a user, I want to log into my account securely so that I can access my finances without fear of fraud or unauthorized access.

## Acceptance Criteria
- ✅ Users must verify identity before accessing any account data
- ✅ Login screen with "forgot password" and "create account" options
- ✅ Multiple failed attempts trigger temporary lockout
- ✅ Successful logins are logged in the system
- ✅ Option to log out anytime

## Security Notes
- Encrypt passwords using industry standards (e.g., bcrypt)
- Use HTTPS for all login-related communication
- Store session tokens securely
- Log and monitor login attempts for suspicious activity
